X:2716151
T:Glenn Towle
C:Dudley Laufman
S:Canterbury Country Dance Orchestra, $2Mistwold.$0 F&W Records, F&W 5, 1974.
H:Glenn Towle was a young and enthusiastic dancer who unfortunately died of
H:leukemia at a young age. Dudley wrote this tune in his honor.
H:There is also a transcription in G, from a recording of a Canterbury Orchestra
H:reunion in 1992. The melody is about the same but there are some differences
H:in chord choices.
