T:Valse Aldor
C:Aldor Morin (1921-1998) or Fortunat Malouin (1870-1935) (maybe)
S:Aldor Morin, $2Collection Les Grands Folkloristes QuÃ©bÃ©cois.$0 Disques MÃ©rite 1376
S:(Copie MaÃ®tre London Records Et Bonanza), CD compilation, 2006.
S:Much of this information comes from a nice article about him at:
S:http://mnemo.qc.ca/bulletin-mnemo/article/aldor-morin-harmoniciste-calleur.
H:This is a transcription of Aldor Morin playing the tune on harmonica. I include
H:a few attempts at transcribing harmonica ornamentation, but didn't try to be
H:complete in part for reasons of legibility, and in part due to my limited ability
H:to transcribe many of the details. Chords are transcribed from the recording as
H:accurately as I could.
H:
H:Aldor Morin got started playing harmonica at the age of 6. He learned harmonica 
H:from Madame Bolduc and by the age of 7 was playing out around QuÃ©bec. He played 
H:with Jean Carignan, Tommy Duschesne and Isidore Soucy among others. He was also 
H:known as a caller, and he wrote a number of excellent tunes. 
